tr: any of various soft sweet desserts thickened usually with flour and baked or boiled or steamed
(British) the dessert course of a meal (`pud' is used informally)
any of various soft thick unsweetened baked dishes

value.def: A pudding is a cooked sweet food made with flour, fat, and eggs, and usually served hot.

example.ex: ...a cherry sponge pudding with warm custard.
example.tran: 涂着热蛋奶沙司的樱桃松糕布丁

value.def: Some people refer to the sweet course of a meal as the pudding.

example.ex: ...a menu featuring canapes, a starter, a main course and a pudding...
example.tran: 一份包含开胃面包、头道菜、主菜和甜点的菜单

example.ex: I tend to stick to fresh fruit for pudding.
example.tran: 我一直坚持用新鲜水果做甜点。

value.def: If you say the proof of the pudding or the proof of the pudding is in the eating, you mean that something new can only be judged to be good or bad after it has been tried or used.
value.tran: 布丁好坏，不尝不知；试过才知好坏
